   <refnamediv>
       <refname>fusvect</refname>
               <refpurpose>sorted fusion of vectors </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[ind]=fusvect(arg1,...,argn)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
           <term>Input</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> arg1,...,argn </term> =   (n x 1) vectors </para></listitem>
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> ind </term> =   a (n x 1) vector</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Makes the fusion of (n x1) vectors and sort them in increasing order.

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
fusvect([1 ;4 ; 5],[3 ; 2 ;4])
// Returns: 
//!   1. !//!   2. !//!   3. !//!   4. !//!   4. !//!   5. !  

               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
        </refsection>
</refentry>
